Hearts by Faith, with Thank&s;giving&mdash;For Je|&s;us Chri&s;t's Sake, do not with one Con&s;ent begin to make Excu&s;e.&mdash;Do not let a Piece of Ground, five Yoke of Oxen, or even a Wife, keep you from this great Supper&mdash;The&s;e you may enjoy, as the Gifts of God, and make u&s;e of them for the Mediator's Glory, and yet be pre&s;ent at the Go&s;pel-Fea&s;t.&mdash;True and unde|filed Religion does not take away, but greatly enhance the Comforts of Life; and our Lord did not pray, that we &s;hould be taken out of the World, but that we &s;hould be delivered from the Evil of it.&mdash;Oh then that you wou'd all, with one Con&s;ent, &s;ay, Lo! we come&mdash;A&s;&s;ure your&s;elves there is Provi&s;ion enough&mdash;For it is a great Supper&mdash;In our Father's Hou&s;e there is Bread enough, and to &s;pare.&mdash;And tho' it is a great God, that makes the Supper, yet he is as Good and Conde&s;cending, as he is Great. Tho' he be the High and Lofty One that inhabiteth Eternity, yet he will dwell with the humble and contrite Heart, even with the Man that trembleth at his Word. Nei|ther can you complain for Want of Room; <HI>for yet there is Room. In our Father's Hou&s;e are many Man&s;ions.</HI> If it was not &s;o, our Sa|viour would have told us. The Grace of Chri&s;t, is as Rich, as Free, and as powerful as ever&mdash;He is the &s;ame Ye&s;terday, to Day, and for ever: He is full of Grace and Truth, and out of his Fulne&s;s, all that come to him
<PB N="69" REF="005885_0081_1027604DD432C2D8">
may receive Grace for Grace&mdash;He giveth li|berally, and upbraideth not&mdash;He willeth not the Death of a Sinner, but that he &s;hould rather Believe and Live.&mdash;Come then, all ye Halt, Poor, Maimed, and Blind Sinners; take Comfort, the Lord Je&s;us hath &s;ent his Servant to call you&mdash;It is now Supper-time, and a Day of uncommon<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Grace. It may be, the Day may be far &s;pent&mdash;Ha&s;te, therefore, and a|way to the Supper of the Lamb&mdash;If you do not come, I know the Ma&s;ter will be angry.&mdash;And who can &s;tand before him, when he is angry? <HI>Harden not therefore your Hearts, as in the Day of Provocation, as in the Day of Temptation in the Wilderne&s;s</HI>&mdash;Do not provoke the Lord to &s;ay, <HI>none of tho&s;e that were bidden &s;hall ta&s;te of my Supper.</HI>&mdash;Oh dreadful Words! Much more is implied in them than is expre&s;&s;ed.&mdash;It is the fame with that in the P&s;alms&mdash;<HI>I &s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">are in my Wrath that they &s;hould not enter into my Re&s;t</HI>&mdash;And if you do not enter into God's Re&s;t, if you do not ta&s;te of Chri&s;t's Supper, you mu&s;t lift up your Eyes in Torments, where you will have no Re&s;t, but mu&s;t &s;up with the damned De|vils for evermore.&mdash;Knowing therefore the Terrors of the Lord, we per&s;uade you to ha&s;te away, and make no more frivolous Excu&s;es&mdash;For there is no Excu&s;e again&s;t Believing.&mdash;Perhaps you may &s;ay&mdash;You call to the Halt, and Maimed, and Blind, and Poor&mdash;But if we
<PB N="70" REF="005885_0082_102760550CE66DE0">
are <HI>Halt,</HI> and <HI>Maimed,</HI> how can we come? If we are <HI>Blind,</HI> how can we <HI>&s;ee our Way?</HI> If we are <HI>Poor,</HI> how can we expect Admi&s;&s;ion to &s;o great a Table? Ah! dear Hearts&mdash;Hap|py are ye, if you are &s;en&s;ible, that you are Halt, and Maimed.&mdash;For if you feel your &s;elves &s;o, and are lamenting it, who knows but whil&s;t I am &s;peaking, God may &s;end his Spirit with the Word, and fetch you home? Tho' you are Blind, Je&s;us has Eye-&s;alve to anoint you&mdash;Tho' you are Poor, yet you are welcome to this rich Fea&s;t&mdash;It co&s;t Je&s;us Chri&s;t a great Price, but you &s;hall have it <HI>gra|tis</HI>&mdash;For &s;uch as you was it de&s;igned&mdash;<HI>Ble&s;&s;ed are the Poor in Spirit, for theirs is the King|dom of Heaven</HI>&mdash;Rich, and Self-righteous, Self-&s;ufficient Sinners, I know, will &s;corn both the Fea&s;t, and its great Provider&mdash;They have done &s;o already, therefore the Lord has &s;ent us into the Highways, and Hedges to bring &s;uch poor Souls as you are in&mdash;Venture then, my dear Friends, and honour God, by taking him at his Word&mdash;Come to the Marriage-Fea&s;t&mdash;Believe me, you will there partake of mo&s;t delicious Fare&mdash;Tell me, ye that have been made to ta&s;te, that the Lord is gracious, will you not recommend this Fea&s;t to all? Are you not, whil&s;t I am &s;peaking, ready to cry out, come all ye that are without, come ye, obey the Call, for we have &s;at under the Re|deemer's Shadow with great Delight, and his
<PB N="71" REF="005885_0083_10276057E9594038">
Fruit has been plea&s;ant to our Ta&s;te&mdash;Whil&s;t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;peaking, does not the Fire kindle, do <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> your Hearts burn with a De&s;ire that others <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> come and be ble&s;&s;ed too? If you are Chri&s;ti|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters"> indeed; I know you will be thus minded, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the Language of your Hearts will be, Lord, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">hil&s;t he is calling, let thy Spirit compel them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> come in.&mdash;Oh that the Lord may &s;ay, <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">!</HI>&mdash;And why &s;hou'd we doubt? Surely <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ur Saviour will not <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">et me complain this Day, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> I have laboured in vain, and &s;pent my <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">rength for nought&mdash;Methinks I &s;ee ma|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters"> de&s;iring to come&mdash;O how &s;hall I compel <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to come forwards&mdash;I will not u&s;e Fire, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Sword, as the <HI>Papi&s;ts</HI> do, by terribly per|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="4 letters">ting this Text of Scripture&mdash;But I will tell <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of the Love of God, the Love of God in Chri&s;t, and &s;urely <HI>that</HI> mu&s;t compel you, <HI>that</HI> mu&s;t con&s;train you, whether you will or not.&mdash;Sinners, my Heart is enlarged towards you&mdash;I could fill my Mouth with Arguments&mdash;Con&s;ider the Greatne&s;s of <HI>the God,</HI> that makes the Supper&mdash;Con&s;ider the Greatne&s;s of <HI>the Price,</HI> wherewith it was purcha&s;ed&mdash;Con&s;i|der the Greatne&s;s of the <HI>Provi&s;ion</HI> made for you&mdash;What would you have more?&mdash;Con&s;ider God's infinite <HI>Conde&s;cen&s;ion,</HI> in calling you now, when you might have been in Hell, <HI>where the Worm dieth not, and the Fire is not quenched.</HI>&mdash;And that you might be without Excu&s;e, he has &s;ent his Servant into the <HI>Highways</HI> and
<PB N="72" REF="005885_0084_102760598A0F2260">
<HI>Hedges,</HI> to invite you there&mdash;Oh that you on|ly ta&s;ted what I do now! I am &s;ure, you wou'd not want Arguments to induce you to come in: No, you wou'd fly to the Go&s;pel-Fea&s;t, as Doves to the Windows.&mdash;But, poor Souls! many of you, perhaps, are not hungry&mdash;You do not feel your &s;elves <HI>Ha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">t,</HI> or <HI>Mai|med,</HI> or <HI>Blind,</HI> and therefore you have no Re|li&s;h for this &s;piritual Entertainment&mdash;Well, be not angry with me for calling you; be not offended, if I weep over you, becau&s;e you know not the Day of your Vi&s;itation; If I mu&s;t appear in Judgment as a &s;wift Witne&s;s again&s;t you, I mu&s;t&mdash;But Oh that Thought chills my Blood!&mdash;I cannot bear it; I fed that I could lay down my Life for you&mdash;But Oh! I am not willing to go without you.&mdash;What &s;ay you, my dear Friends? I wou'd put the Que&s;tion to you once more&mdash;Will you ta&s;te of Chri&s;t's Supper, or will you not? You &s;hall all be welcome. There is Milk at this Fea&s;t for Babes, as well as Meat for &s;trong Men, and Per&s;ons of riper Years&mdash;There's Room and Provi&s;ion for High and Low, Rich and Poor, one with another; and our Saviour will thank you for coming&mdash;Amazing Con|de&s;cen&s;ion!&mdash;A&s;toni&s;hing Love!&mdash;The Thought of it quite overcomes me&mdash;Help me, help me, O Believers, to ble&s;s and prai&s;e him&mdash;And Oh! that his Love may excite us to come afre&s;h to him, as tho' we had never
<PB N="73" REF="005885_0085_1027605C7AC0E8A8">
come before! For, tho' we have been often fea&s;ted, yet our Souls will &s;tarve, unle&s;s we renew our Acts of Faith, and throw our&s;elves, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> lo&s;t, undone Sinners, continually at the Feet of Chri&s;t.&mdash;Feeding upon pa&s;t Experiences will not &s;atisfy our Souls any more, than what we eat Ye&s;terday will &s;u&s;tain our Bodies to Day.&mdash;No, Believers mu&s;t look for fre&s;h In|fluences of divine Grace, and beg of the Lord, to water them every Moment&mdash;The Parable therefore &s;peaks to Saints, as well as Sinners.&mdash;Come ye to the Marriage-fea&s;t; you are as welcome now as ever&mdash;And may God &s;et your Souls a longing for that Time, when we &s;hall, &s;it down and eat Bread in the Kingdom of Heaven!&mdash;There we &s;hall have full Draughts of Heaven&mdash;There we &s;hall have full Draughts of divine Love, and enjoy the glorious Ema|nuel, without intermi&s;&s;ion, for evermore.&mdash;Even &s;o Lord Je&s;us, <HI>Amen.</HI></P>
